INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2013-11-19 03:08:11','2013-11-19 03:08:11','&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWelcome to the world of Firasimus. I\'ll be using this website to document my \"adventures\" that take place while trying to learn Linux as efficiently as possible. By adventures, I mean lost the remainder of my hair and about 5 years of my life stressing over a problem that\'s probably fixable within two lines of code. It\'s also just a really clever way to allow me to go back and check on problems I\'ve figured out. Before we get started I\'ll have to set up a theme for all of this.\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">What do I mean by theme? Well, I am Firasimus and I am a badass virtual gladiator that will slay all the combatants, which in this case, are Linux problems. I was given this name by a Persian Prince and it\'s stuck ever since. My mentor in this world will be named Azretximo. Azretximo will eventually send me to Rome to slay all the virtual gladiators so that I may win my freedom.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">No, but seriously, let\'s just start. I began this morning by transferring the domain name from legacyuo.com to firasimus.com. I was preemptive and began changing the conf files located in Nginx to prepare for the move. All I had to do was make :</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Server {</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Listen 80;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">server_name www.legacyuo.com legacyuo.com;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Into:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Server {</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Listen 80;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">server_name firasimus.com www.firasimus.com;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Easy enough.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Everything seemed to have been working except for the fact that my Wordpress /wp-admin was pointing to my old domain name. It was an easy fix. Log into Admin,  Go to Settings and change the of Wordpress Address(URL) and Site Address (URL) to the corresponding domain name.</p>\r\nFor now, that\'s it. I\'ll be posting problems/results as they occur.\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr valign=\"top\">\r\n<th scope=\"row\"></th>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"top\">\r\n<th scope=\"row\"></th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>','And so it begins','','publish','open','open','','hello-world','','','2013-12-02 01:30:25','2013-12-02 01:30:25','',0,'http://legacyuo.com/?p=1',0,'post','',1),(2,1,'2013-11-19 03:08:11','2013-11-19 03:08:11','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://legacyuo.com/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','publish','open','open','','sample-page','','','2013-11-19 03:08:11','2013-11-19 03:08:11','',0,'http://legacyuo.com/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(4,1,'2013-11-29 02:03:26','2013-11-29 02:03:26','Before we begin I\'d just like to point out that I am a pretty \"crude\" individual. If you have a problem with that then get the fuck off this website, thanks.\n\nThat being said, welcome to the world of Firasimus. I\'ll be using this website to document my \"adventures\" that take place while trying to le